  "build": {
    "buildCommand": "cd /Users/mac/cat/catwallet-ops-backend\ngh pr create --base main --head feature/i18n-upload-app-frontend \\\n  --title \"feat(admin-web): add app package upload UI to i18n page\" \\\n  --body \"$(cat <<'EOF'\n## Summary\nWires up the admin-web frontend for the `uploadApp` backend endpoint (already on main in 577d446). Previously the permission string and backend route existed but there was no UI to invoke them — a user granted `i18n:upload_app` had no way to use it.\n\n## Changes\n- `i18nApi.uploadApp()` — posts `multipart/form-data` (field `file`) to `POST /i18n/uploadApp`, with a 130s client timeout to match the backend's 120s upstream budget for large APKs (default client timeout is 35s).\n- i18n toolbar gains a permission-gated **Upload App Package** button (`.apk`), shown only when the user holds `i18n:upload_app` (superadmin bypasses). Backend `@RequirePermission` remains the real enforcement.\n- Records an `upload_app` op-log entry on success (filename + size), consistent with batch import.\n- zh/en locale strings for the button and success toast.\n\n## Testing\n- `tsc -p apps/admin-web --noEmit` clean\n- `npm run build` (admin-web) succeeds\n- Locale JSON validated\n\n## Deploy note\nFrontend-only. Requires rebuilding + deploying the admin-web container (`docker compose up -d --build admin-web`). The `i18n:upload_app` permission must also be seeded on the server for the button to appear for non-superadmins.\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\nEOF\n)\" 2>&1 | tail -10",
    "testCommand": "npx jest auth i18n 2>&1 | tail -30",
    "lintCommand": "npm run lint",
    "devCommand": "npm run start",
    "scripts": {
      "build": "nest build && tsc -p tsconfig.seed.json",
      "start": "node dist/main",
      "start:dev": "nest start --watch",
      "lint": "eslint \"apps/**/*.ts\" --fix",
      "typecheck": "tsc --noEmit",
